.TH MORSE 1 "March 2026" "morse" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
morse \- encode text to Morse code or decode Morse code to text
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B morse
[\fIOPTION\fR] \fItext\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B morse
encodes plain text to Morse code by default.

Use
.B --decode
to convert Morse code back into text.

Letters and digits are supported. Spaces are encoded as
.B /
and unsupported input is emitted as
.BR ? .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-decode
Decode Morse code into text.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show a short usage message and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Encode text:
.B morse SOS
.br
Produces:
.B ... --- ...
.TP
Decode Morse code:
.B morse --decode "... --- ..."
.br
Produces:
.B SOS
.TP
Decode Morse code with a word break:
.B morse --decode "... --- ... / .---- ..--- ...--"
.br
Produces:
.B SOS 123
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid usage, such as missing required arguments.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR man (1)
